Five pairs of preclitellar 
nephridia
from 5/6 to 9/10 (Fig. 
2A
); each about 160 mm long and 60 mm wide (
in vivo
). Anteseptale globular, with minute and numerous brownish granules at periphery; funnel orientated obliquely ventrad, with small and narrow anterior projection; postseptale elongate, ca twice as long as anteseptale. Efferent duct originating from the middle of the postseptale (Fig. 
3G
).
